OL,6,FHow did this appeal get to the Supreme
OL,7,FCourt?
OL,9,FThe Court of Session ruled that
OL,10,Fchanging the definition of a woman in
OL,11,Fthe act was unlawful, as it dealt with
OL,12,Fmatters falling outside the Scottish
OL,13,FParliament's legal competence.
OL,15,FFollowing the challenge, the Scottish
OL,16,FGovernment dropped the definition from
OL,17,Fthe act and issued revised advice on
OL,18,Fhow to comply with the law.
