OL,6,FThis stated that under the 2018 Act
OL,7,Fthe definition of a woman was the same
OL,8,Fas that set out in the Equality Act
OL,9,F2010, and that a person with a GRC
OL,10,Frecognising their gender as female had
OL,11,Fthe sex of a woman.
OL,13,FFWS challenged this revised guidance
OL,14,Fon the grounds that sex under the
OL,15,FEquality Act referred to its
OL,16,Fbiological meaning, and the government
OL,17,Fwas overstepping its powers by
OL,18,Feffectively redefining the meaning of
OL,19,F"woman".
